<div class="full-width-container faq-section" style="background-color: #F9F9F9; padding: 60px 0;">
    <!-- Reduced padding -->
    <h2 style="text-align: center; font-size: 2rem; color: #333;">Common Questions About ABA Therapy</h2> <!-- Reduced font-size -->
    <div class="faq-container" style="max-width: 1000px; margin: 40px auto;">
        <!-- Reduced margin and max-width -->
        <!-- FAQ 1 -->
        <div class="faq-item" style="margin-bottom: 15px; border: 1px solid #7031E3; border-radius: 10px; overflow: hidden; padding: 15px;">
            <!-- Reduced margins, border size, and padding -->
            <h3 style="color: #7031E3;">What does ABA stand for?</h3>
            <p>ABA is an acronym for Applied Behavior Analysis, also referred to as Behavioral Engineering. The ABA method is made up of scientifically progressive techniques used to improve or correct certain types of behavior. Working with children within the autism spectrum, the therapy has proven success in managing problematic behavior while developing social and academic skills.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 2 -->
        <div class="faq-item" style="margin-bottom: 15px; border: 1px solid #7031E3; border-radius: 10px; overflow: hidden; padding: 15px;">
            <h3 style="color: #7031E3;">What does BCBA stand for?</h3>
            <p>BCBA stands for Board Certified Behavior Analyst. BCBAs are professionals who specialize in behavior analysis, often working with individuals on the autism spectrum to improve social behaviors and reduce problematic behaviors.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 3 -->
        <div class="faq-item" style="margin-bottom: 15px; border: 1px solid #7031E3; border-radius: 10px; overflow: hidden; padding: 15px;">
            <h3 style="color: #7031E3;">Can you give me specific examples of behavior that ABA therapy focuses on?</h3>
            <p>ABA therapy can help children improve social skills, enhance communication, and reduce problematic behaviors. Examples of targeted behaviors include increasing eye contact, improving social interactions, and reducing self-injurious behaviors.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 4 -->
        <div class="faq-item" style="margin-bottom: 15px; border: 1px solid #7031E3; border-radius: 10px; overflow: hidden; padding: 15px;">
            <h3 style="color: #7031E3;">Is there an age-appropriate time to begin ABA therapy?</h3>
            <p>ABA therapy can be beneficial for children of various ages, depending on their needs. Early intervention is often recommended, but ABA can also help older children and adults improve their skills and reduce problematic behaviors.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 5 -->
        <div class="faq-item" style="margin-bottom: 15px; border: 1px solid #7031E3; border-radius: 10px; overflow: hidden; padding: 15px;">
            <h3 style="color: #7031E3;">How do I know if my child needs ABA therapy?</h3>
            <p>Consulting with a developmental specialist or a BCBA can help determine whether ABA therapy is right for your child. Common signs that ABA may be beneficial include delayed communication skills, difficulty with social interactions, and repetitive behaviors.</p>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>

